===message:Proposal number 1: 
     I don't think that it would be a good idea for the United States government to give away our surplus grain to other countries.  One reason is that surplus doesn't necessarily mean that our country is satisfied.  There are always going to be starving people in our country.  It doesn’t help them any if we give away food that could be helping them.  As well, what would happen if we did give away all of our grain and we were struck with some kind of devastation.  Perhaps Florida again gets hit with a killer hurricane, in which they need help from the government feeding the children.  How would we be able to protect and help those individuals in need without any grain in reserves.  Finally, this is kind of an off the wall reason, but if we give our grain away and then enter a world war, in which we must ration what is left of the grain.  How can we fight for ourselves or another country when we can't even take care of ourselves.
<br>
Proposal #2:
	I don’t believe that it is a good idea, nor is it a possible idea for the entire country to became vegetarians.  It is not a good idea because every time that you try to fix something another problem usually develops.  If we decide to cut out meat entirely from out diet, we then must plan a way to provide the people with more protein.  This can be hard to do because there aren’t too many choices to go with.  Along with this if we decide to do this it means changing our eating habits and nutrients all together.  While this could greatly help some people it might be destroying others.  If people do not get the correct amount of protein and other amounts of nutrients we could be dealing with a higher death rate, which would create an number of other problems.  As for the other part, it would be impossible for the government to force something like this on the American people.  Frist of all it would not be practical in that it would be very hard to enforce it.  there are always going to be people to find a way to get around it. Also I think that there would be a very large rebellion from the people.  It is one of our rights to be able to choose what we want to eat. If the government tries to take this away from us there is going to be a loud outcry.

