I dont think we should all become vegetarians just to feed the world, instead resources should be put into making more land avaiable for grazing, making harmful chemicals and pesticides illegal so it does not destroy the land. And like I said in Proposal 1, us becoming vegetarians to feed the less fortunate will work and do some good for the immediate future but what happens when other countries dependance on us which leads to increased production, which leads to demand which has been unheard of. Add in the fact that we would be losing proteins and that the receiving countries would not be receiving enough proteins to make up for years of malnutrition and hunger makes the idea very foolish. Instead of changing eating habits to vegetarian it would be more beneficial to invest funds into vaccines and other medicines that will allow these unfortunate poorer cultures to grow and fend for themselves, we should help them out but not give away everything when the returns will be nothing but loss for the US

